#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.75"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.75:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.75:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga "
msgstr "8. Sick "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.75:0.3"
msgid "75. Dutiyagilānasutta "
msgstr "75. Sick (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.75:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.75:1.2"
msgid "“amukasmiṃ, bhante, vihāre aññataro bhikkhu navo appaññāto ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "“Sir, in such and such a monastery there’s a mendicant who is junior and not well-known. He’s sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:1.3"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Please go to him out of compassion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.75:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā navavādañca sutvā gilānavādañca, “appaññāto bhikkhū”ti iti viditvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "When the Buddha heard that the mendicant was junior and ill, understanding that he was not well-known, he went to him. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "That mendicant saw the Buddha coming off in the distance "

msgctxt "sn35.75:2.3"
msgid "Disvāna mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "and tried to rise on his cot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.75:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to that monk, "

msgctxt "sn35.75:2.5"
msgid "“alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā tvaṃ mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "“It’s all right, mendicant, don’t get up. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:2.6"
msgid "Santimāni āsanāni paññattāni, tatthāhaṃ nisīdissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "There are some seats spread out, I will sit there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.75:2.7"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane. Nisajja kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He sat on the seat spread out and said to the mendicant, "

msgctxt "sn35.75:2.8"
msgid "“kacci te, bhikkhu, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ, kacci dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti no abhikkamanti, paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati no abhikkamo”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope you’re keeping well, mendicant; I hope you’re alright. I hope that your pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.75:3.1"
msgid "“Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "“Sir, I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: maṃ → me (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn35.75:3.2"
msgid "na kho maṃ, bhante, attā sīlato upavadatī”ti. "
msgstr "I have no reason to blame myself when it comes to ethical conduct.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.75:4.1"
msgid "“No ce kira te, bhikkhu, attā sīlato upavadati, atha kiñca te kukkuccaṃ ko ca vippaṭisāro”ti? "
msgstr "“In that case, mendicant, why do you have remorse and regret?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.75:5.1"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, bhante, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Because I understand that the Buddha has not taught the Dhamma merely for the sake of ethical purity.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.48, sc6
msgctxt "sn35.75:6.1"
msgid "“No ce kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi, atha kimatthaṃ carahi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsī”ti? "
msgstr "“If that is so, what exactly do you understand to be the purpose of teaching the Dhamma?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.75:7.1"
msgid "“Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I understand that the Buddha has taught the Dhamma for the purpose of complete extinguishment by not grasping.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.75:8.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu. "
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicant! "

msgctxt "sn35.75:8.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ mayā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi. "
msgstr "It’s good that you understand that I’ve taught the Dhamma for the purpose of complete extinguishment by not grasping. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:8.3"
msgid "Anupādāparinibbānattho hi, bhikkhu, mayā dhammo desito. "
msgstr "For that is indeed the purpose. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.75:9.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicant? "

msgctxt "sn35.75:9.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.75:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.75:11.1"
msgid "“… pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.2"
msgid "Sotaṃ … "
msgstr "“Is the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.3"
msgid "ghānaṃ … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.4"
msgid "jivhā … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.5"
msgid "kāyo … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.6"
msgid "mano … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.7"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "mind consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.8"
msgid "manosamphasso … "
msgstr "mind contact … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:11.9"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.75:12.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.75:13.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.75:14.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.75:15.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.75:15.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.75:16.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "sn35.75:17.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhu, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye … ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:17.2"
msgid "manasmimpi … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:17.3"
msgid "manoviññāṇepi … "
msgstr "mind consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:17.4"
msgid "manosamphassepi nibbindati. "
msgstr "mind contact … "

msgctxt "sn35.75:17.5"
msgid "Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:17.6"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.75:17.7"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn35.75:18.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn35.75:18.2"
msgid "Attamano so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandi. "
msgstr "Satisfied, that mendicant was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. VAR: vimuccīti → vimuccatīti (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.75:18.3"
msgid "Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tassa bhikkhussa anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccīti. "
msgstr "And while this discourse was being spoken, the mind of that mendicant was freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.75:18.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

